"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444375","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-01-22","<p>As I have made clear in previous answers on this subject the UK Government is committed to affording due respect and parity of esteem to all the people in Northern Ireland as underpinned by the 1998 Belfast Agreement, and in accordance with the obligations on the Government to promote equality and prevent discrimination across the United Kingdom.</p><br />",,"Lord Dunlop","HL4978 ; HL4979 ; HL4980 ; HL4981 ; HL4982","2016-01-22T12:08:21.51Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444375/answer","Biography information for Lord Dunlop","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444375/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444375/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-01-12","Equality: Northern Ireland","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether members of the security forces who served in Northern Ireland are entitled to parity of esteem on the same basis as those from Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Lord Laird",,"Lord Laird","HL4983"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445254","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-18","<p>We are determined that many more young people benefit from the Cadets experience. Hence we have committed an extra £50 million to increase the number of Cadet Units in schools across the UK to 500 by 2020.</p><br /><p>More widely, the Community Cadet Forces continue to recruit new Cadets. Over 3,000 Community Cadet Force Units provide exceptional opportunities for over 131,000 young people to develop key life skills.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2016-01-18T17:41:16.467Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445254/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445254/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445254/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-12","Armed Forces: Cadets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he is taking to encourage recruitment of cadets.","false","Biography information for Mark Garnier","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier","903070"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445255","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-18","<p>I am not currently engaged in any discussions with my Russian counterpart. The illegal annexation of Crimea in 2014 and Russia’s continuing support to separatists in eastern Ukraine do not allow a return to normal engagement.</p><p>However, in the interests of Air and Maritime safety, I have authorised MOD officials to undertake limited military to military engagement with the Russians, which is now in progress.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2016-01-18T17:39:47.063Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445255/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445255/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445255/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-12","Russia: Defence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions he is having with his Russian counterpart on improving collaboration on defence affairs.","false","Biography information for Daniel Kawczynski","Shrewsbury and Atcham","Daniel Kawczynski","903064"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445258","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-18","<p>The Strategic Defence and Security Review provided clarity of the Government’s defence equipment priorities not just for the next two years, but for the rest of this Parliament. We have committed to an additional £12 billion for the Equipment Plan to £178 billion over the next 10 years. This includes finalising investment proposals for the next stage of the Successor nuclear deterrent programme and the procurement of a new fleet of nine Boeing P8 Maritime Patrol Aircraft, as we build towards Joint Force 2025.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-01-18T17:42:24.887Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445258/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445258/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445258/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-12","Defence Equipment: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what his priorities are for the acquisition of defence equipment over the next two years.","false","Biography information for Sir Gerald Howarth","Aldershot","Sir Gerald Howarth","903065"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445259","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-18","<p>Between 2 December 2015 and 18 January 2016 there have been five Brimstone missiles used against Daesh targets by the RAF in Syria. There have also been 32 Paveway IV and 6 Hellfire missiles used for the same period in Syria.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2016-01-18T17:39:08.553Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445259/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445259/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445259/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-12","Syria: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Brimstone missiles have been used by the RAF in Syria since 2 December 2015.","false","Biography information for Carol Monaghan","Glasgow North West","Carol Monaghan","903067"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445260","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-18","<p>Official UK defence export statistics are compiled each year by the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills and the figures for 2015 are not yet available.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-01-18T17:41:46.017Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445260/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445260/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445260/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-12","Saudi Arabia: Arms Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much accrued to the public purse from sales of arms to Saudi Arabia in 2015.","false","Biography information for Patricia Gibson","North Ayrshire and Arran","Patricia Gibson","903071"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445605","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-01-20","<p>The threat from Northern Ireland Related Terrorism is severe.</p><p>It is being suppressed by the hard work of PSNI and MI5. Because of their efforts, the number of national security attacks has fallen from 40 in 2010 to 16 in 2015. But the need for total vigilance remains and will continue.</p><br />","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2016-01-20T16:28:36.11Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445605/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445605/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445605/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-01-12","Security: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what recent assessment she has made of the security situation in Northern Ireland; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Henry Bellingham","North West Norfolk","Sir Henry Bellingham","903074"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446119","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-01-20","<p>Support for charities is a matter for the Northern Ireland Assembly. The Government does however, support the Big Lottery Fund (BIG), which plays a vital role in supporting the charity sector in Northern Ireland.</p><p>The Chancellor announced in the Spending Review that BIG’s funding will be maintained and Northern Ireland will receive £27.3m.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2016-01-20T15:49:14.12Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446119/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446119/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446119/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-01-12","Charities: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what steps the Government is taking to support charities in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Carolyn Harris","Swansea East","Carolyn Harris","903086"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446120","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-01-20","<p>The Government is fulfilling its manifesto commitment to seek a reformed relationship with Europe and then put the results of that negotiation to the people in a referendum.</p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2016-01-20T15:51:26.553Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446120/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446120/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446120/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-01-12","EU Internal Trade: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what assessment she has made of the value to the economy in Northern Ireland of membership of the EU single market.","false","Biography information for Neil Carmichael","Stroud","Neil Carmichael","903085"
