n each constituency in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","21887"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443781","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-18","<p>In 1968, Australia signed an agreement with the UK confirming that the clean-up of all test sites had been completed satisfactorily. As announced to the House on 10 December 1993,(<em>Official Report</em>, column 421), the Government agreed to make an ex gratia payment of £20 million to the Federal Government of Australia as a contribution to the cost of the further clean-up of the Maralinga site. A copy of the note giving effect to this agreement was placed in the Library of the House. The note also records that the Government of Australia indemnified the Government of the UK against claims from Australian nationals or residents. The Government now regards the matter as closed.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-01-18T16:06:03.567Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443781/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443781/answer","Hansard Extract  Friday 10 December 1993.docx","Hansard Extract  Friday 10 December 1993.docx","Maralinga","Maralinga","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443781/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-11","Australia: Nuclear Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if the Government will issue issuing an apology to the indigenous people of Australia for British nuclear tests carried out on their land in the 1950s and 1960s.","false","Biography information for Stewart Malcolm McDonald","Glasgow South","Stewart Malcolm McDonald","21757"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443782","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-14","<p>The number of claims that have been made under the plug-in car grant scheme for each quarter since its introduction is as follows:</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Quarter</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Car Claims </strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jan - Mar 2011</p></td><td><p>462</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Apr - Jun 2011</p></td><td><p>230</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jul - Sept 2011</p></td><td><p>104</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oct - Dec 2011</p></td><td><p>109</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jan - Mar 2012</p></td><td><p>400</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Apr - Jun 2012</p></td><td><p>406</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jul - Sept 2012</p></td><td><p>599</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oct - Dec 2012</p></td><td><p>710</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jan - Mar 2013</p></td><td><p>612</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Apr - Jun 2013</p></td><td><p>920</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jul - Sept 2013</p></td><td><p>1109</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oct - Dec 2013</p></td><td><p>1047</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jan - Mar 2014</p></td><td><p>2015</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Apr - Jun 2014</p></td><td><p>2536</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jul - Sept 2014</p></td><td><p>4889</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oct - Dec 2014</p></td><td><p>5976</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jan - Mar 2015</p></td><td><p>8558</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Apr - Jun 2015</p></td><td><p>6992</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jul - Sept 2015</p></td><td><p>6957</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oct - Dec 2015</p></td><td><p>8453</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>TOTAL</p></td><td><p>53084</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>The number of claims that have been made under the plug-in van grant scheme for each quarter since its introduction is as follows:</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Quarter</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Van Claims </strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jan - Mar 2011</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Apr - Jun 2011</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jul - Sept 2011</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oct - Dec 2011</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jan - Mar 2012</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Apr - Jun 2012</p></td><td><p>99</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jul - Sept 2012</p></td><td><p>41</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oct - Dec 2012</p></td><td><p>75</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jan - Mar 2013</p></td><td><p>49</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Apr - Jun 2013</p></td><td><p>46</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jul - Sept 2013</p></td><td><p>53</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oct - Dec 2013</p></td><td><p>41</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jan - Mar 2014</p></td><td><p>37</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Apr - Jun 2014</p></td><td><p>196</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jul - Sept 2014</p></td><td><p>170</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oct - Dec 2014</p></td><td><p>206</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jan - Mar 2015</p></td><td><p>298</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Apr - Jun 2015</p></td><td><p>251</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jul - Sept 2015</p></td><td><p>163</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oct - Dec 2015</p></td><td><p>181</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>TOTAL</p></td><td><p>1906</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>The total number of car and van grant claims in the fourth quarter of 2015 is still subject to audit.</p><br /><p>These figures do not include claims that have been cancelled.</p><br /><p>I am pleased to note that this Government has recently announced a long-term extension to the<a href="https://www.gov.uk/plug-in-car-van-grants" target="_blank">plug-in car grant</a>, backed by a £400 million package to treble the number of ultra low emission vehicles on Britain’s roads. This means the grant will continue well beyond the latest guarantee of February 2016 until at least the end of March 2018 and will mean more than 100,000 people will benefit over the coming years — double the number who have already claimed the grant since 2011.</p><br />","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-01-14T15:22:35.717Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443782/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443782/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443782/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-11","Electric Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many claims under the plug-in grant scheme for (a) cars and (b) vans have been accepted in each quarter since the introduction of that scheme.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","21898"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443783","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-14","<p>The Office for Budget Responsibility provide the Government with estimates for annual pay growth. The table below sets out their forecast growth in average earnings for the years requested.</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Average earnings growth (per cent)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>3.4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017</p></td><td><p>3.7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2018</p></td><td><p>3.6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2019</p></td><td><p>3.7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2020</p></td><td><p>3.9</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-01-14T14:49:03.773Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443783/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443783/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443783/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-11","Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent estimate he has made of average annual pay growth in (a) 2016, (b) 2017, (c) 2018, (d) 2019 and (e) 2020.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","22002"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443784","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-01-14","<p>The Government has not made an estimate of the National Minimum Wage (NMW) rates for these age groups for each year until 2020.</p><p /> <p>The Government asks the Low Pay Commission to make NMW rate recommendations each year based on maximising the wages of the low paid without damaging employment opportunities. The Low Pay Commission will recommend the October 2016 NMW rates and indicative rates for 2017 by the end of February 2016.</p><p><strong></strong></p><br />","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles","18568","2016-01-14T15:47:29.417Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443784/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443784/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443784/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-11","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Written Questions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, when he plans to provide an answer to Question 18568, tabled by the hon. Member for East Ham on 2 December 2015.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","21821"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443785","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-14","<p>Whilst Eurostar services commenced in 1994, St Pancras has only been the London terminus for HS1 services since late 2007. Eurostar journeys originating from St Pancras are as follows:</p><br /><p>2008 4.3m</p><p>2009 4.3m</p><p>2010 4.6m</p><p>2011 4.7m</p><p>20124.8m</p><p>2013 5.0m</p><p>2014 5.1m</p><p>2015 5.1m</p><br /><p>Domestic high speed services, operated by franchised train company Southeastern, commenced in 2010. Southeastern journeys originating from St Pancras are as follows:</p><br /><p>2010 0.6m</p><p>2011 2.0m</p><p>2012 2.5m</p><p>2013 2.8m</p><p>2014 3.0m</p><p>2015 3.4m</p><br />","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-01-14T15:55:53.417Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443785/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443785/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443785/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-11","St Pancras Station: Passengers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many passengers have used high-speed rail services from London St Pancras station in each year since such services started.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","21962"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443786","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-14","<p>Transport for London’s forecasts indicate that the following passenger numbers will (a) access Crossrail services via Stratford station and (b) pass through Stratford station on Crossrail services in each of the first three years after Crossrail services commence.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><br></p></td><td><p>2019</p></td><td><p>2020</p></td><td><p>2021</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Passenger numbers accessing Crossrail services via Stratford Station</p></td><td><p>7.07m</p></td><td><p>7.18m</p></td><td><p>7.29m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Crossrail passenger numbers using Stratford station as an interchange</p></td><td><p>34.89m</p></td><td><p>35.43m</p></td><td><p>35.96m</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>I have interpreted part ‘b’ of your request as referring to Crossrail passengers who will use Stratford station as an interchange.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-01-14T15:49:48.19Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443786/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443786/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443786/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-11","Stratford Station: Passengers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the number of passengers who will (a) access Crossrail services via Stratford station and (b) pass through Stratford station on Crossrail services in each of the first three years after Crossrail services commence.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","21775"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443787","Department for Education","false","2016-01-19","<p>These are matters for Ofqual, the Office of Qualifications and Examinations Regulation. I have therefore asked its Chief Regulator, Glenys Stacey to write directly to the Honourable Member. A copy of her replies will be placed in the House of Commons Library.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","21748 ; 21750","2016-01-19T11:16:06.757Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443787/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443787/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443787/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-01-11","Assessments: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what proportion of (a) GCSE, (b) AS and (c) A-level exam results have (i) increased, (ii) decreased and (iii) stayed the same following an appeal in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Gareth Johnson","Dartford","Gareth Johnson","21749"
