"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443808","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-01-18","<p>I refer my hon. Friend to the answer given to him by my rt. hon. Friend the Prime Minister on 14 January 2016 to Question 21952:</p><br /><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2016-01-11/21952/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2016-01-11/21952/</a>.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-01-18T15:52:15.183Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443808/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443808/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443808/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-01-11","Department for Energy and Climate Change: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what contingency arrangements her Department has made for the eventuality of a majority leave vote in the upcoming EU referendum.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","21941"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443809","Attorney General","false","2016-01-14","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to the answer given to question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2016-01-11/21952/" target="_blank">21952</a> by my Rt. Hon Friend the Prime Minister on the 14<sup>th</sup> January.</p><br />","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2016-01-14T14:15:19.69Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443809/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443809/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443809/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2016-01-11","Attorney General: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what contingency arrangements the Law Officers' Departments have made for the eventuality of a majority leave vote in the upcoming EU referendum.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","21934"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443810","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-01-18","<p>I refer my hon Friend to the reply given on 14 January by my Rt hon Friend the Prime Minister's answer to UIN <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2016-01-11/21952/" target="_blank">21952</a>.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-01-18T16:15:19.957Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443810/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443810/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443810/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-11","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what contingency arrangements his Department has made for the eventuality of a majority leave vote in the upcoming EU referendum.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","21933"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443811","Church Commissioners","false","2016-01-15","<p>The Church Commissioners and the Church of England Pensions Board manage their investment portfolios using high quality well diversified and long term strategies. The Church Commissioners and Pensions Board believe that they are well positioned for any market re-pricing or uncertainty that may prevail prior to or after the referendum.</p><br />","Meriden","Mrs Caroline Spelman",,"2016-01-15T09:53:04.213Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443811/answer","Biography information for Dame Caroline Spelman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443811/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443811/answer",,,,,"9","Church Commissioners","Church Commissioners","2016-01-11","Church Commissioners: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the right hon. Member for Meriden, representing the Church Commissioners, what contingency arrangements the Church Commissioners have made for the eventuality of a majority leave vote in the upcoming EU referendum.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","21936"
